    A major engineering gap we identified is robustness in low-light and adverse weather. The **GMU/UT Austin (Xiao/Song)** lineage has pioneered **SparseVideoNav (2025)**, which is the first foundational realization of "Beyond-the-View" navigation in challenging night scenes. Complementary work like **MVLR (2025)** provides a VLM-based restoration bank to "clean" visual input from rain or snow before it hits your navigation policy.

