    For an engineer, the most important papers are the 2025/26 "red-teaming" evaluations. **VLA-Arena** and the study **"Can Vision Foundation Models Navigate?"** warn that even the best models (ViNT, NoMaD) suffer from systematic collisions in cluttered spaces and perceptual aliasing (hallucinating paths) in repetitive outdoor environments. They recommend using **SafeVLA (2025)**, which embeds explicit safety constraints during training to minimize these "long-tail" risks.

